## The blocking call

Finding `crime_00023` (Sync I/O in Hot Path) in `src/api/files.ts`, inside `loadPlanSchema`. Evidence verbatim:

> - `` `existsSync` @L12 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function) ``
> - `` `statSync` @L13 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function) ``
> - `` `readFileSync` @L15 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function) ``
> - lines: 12, 13, 15
> - swap for the async variant (`readFile`, `writeFile`, `exec`, …) and `await` it

Three `fs` sync methods — **`existsSync`**, **`statSync`**, **`readFileSync`** — fire on every request. Each one parks the entire event loop until the kernel returns, which is exactly the p99/event-loop-lag signature you're seeing under concurrent load. Caching would mask it; the call itself is the bug.

## Smallest async migration

Keep the name and parameters of `loadPlanSchema` identical; flip it to `async` so the only signature change is the implicit `Promise<T>` wrapper (already awaitable by any caller that wasn't actively relying on synchronous return).

```ts
// before
import { existsSync, statSync, readFileSync } from "node:fs";

export function loadPlanSchema(path: string) {
  if (!existsSync(path)) throw new Error(`missing schema: ${path}`);
  const stat = statSync(path);
  // ...size/mtime checks...
  const buf = readFileSync(path, "utf8");
  return JSON.parse(buf);
}

// after
import { readFile, stat } from "node:fs/promises";

export async function loadPlanSchema(path: string) {
  let info;
  try {
    info = await stat(path);                       // replaces existsSync + statSync
  } catch (err: any) {
    if (err.code === "ENOENT") throw new Error(`missing schema: ${path}`);
    throw err;
  }
  // ...size/mtime checks using `info`...
  const buf = await readFile(path, "utf8");        // replaces readFileSync
  return JSON.parse(buf);
}
```

Two notes on the shape of the fix:

1. **Collapse `existsSync` + `statSync` into one `await stat()`.** Beyond unblocking the loop, this kills the TOCTOU race between the existence check and the read, and drops the per-request syscall count from 3 → 2.
2. **Any caller of `loadPlanSchema` now needs to `await` it.** That's the only ripple — the parameter list, name, and resolved value are unchanged. If the handler in `src/api/files.ts` wasn't already `async`, mark it so and `await` the call site; nothing else in the public surface moves.
